<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469067>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Beauchampia crucigera attached to filamentous algae. A. Corona retracted; B. corona expanded. Bar = 500 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469067/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469069>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Scanning electron photomicrograph (SEM) of part of a colony of Sinantherina socialis. The two individuals in the center show the oviferon (OV) below the cloaca (CL). A gelatinous matrix is absent in this genus. (Bar ~ 250 µm.)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469069/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469071>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Examples of species in the genus Limnias: A-B. solitary Limnias ceratophylli-group; C. solitary Limnias melicerta- group; D. colonial L. ceratophylli-group; E. colonial L. melicerta-group. Symbols: a = algae; e = embryo; S = substratum. Bars ~ 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469071/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469073>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Octotrocha speciosa. A. dorsal view; B. partial side view which illustrates the elaborate coronal lobes. Symbol: g = gelatinous matrix (tube). Bar = 250 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469073/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469075>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Lacinularoides coloniensis: schematic dorsal view of the corona. Ciliation is indicated for only a small portion of the coronal margin. Bar = 250 µm. (Modified after Colledge, 1918)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469075/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469077>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Examples of Floscularia species. A. Floscularia melicerta B. F Floscularia conifera (lateral view). Symbols an = antennae; c = corona; e = embryo; gt = gelatinous tube; pt = pellet tube; * = colony mates (out of focus). Bars = 500 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469077/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469079>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Examples of Ptygura species. A. Ptygura beauchampi Edmondson, 1940; B. Ptygura libera Myers, 1934; C. Ptygura brachiata (Hudson, 1886); D. Ptygura mucicola (Kellicott, 1889); E. Ptygura pilula (Cubitt, 1872). Symbols: an = antennae; c = corona; e = embryo; gt = gelatinous tube; fp = fecal pellets (embedded in gt); gl = Gloeotrichia sp. (cyanobacteria) attached to a vascular hydrophyte; S = substratum.. Bars = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469079/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469081>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Examples of Lacinularia. A. SEM dorsal view; B. Complete colony attached to Ceratophyllum demersum Linnaeus, 1753; C. Closeup of a colony. Symbols: a = algal filament; b = body; c = corona; gm = gelatinous matrix (embryos are embedded within); m = mouth; S = substratum. Bars = 1,000 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469081/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

